Author: TechBench
Title: [ANN][Pre-ICO] TechBench — Social network for professionals, investors & B2B HR
Body: WEBSITE | WHITEPAPER | Crowdsale portal [LIVE] ✧ Bounty portal ✧  PRESALE START: September 5th, 2017 | PRESALE END: October 25th, 2017 | PRESALE BONUS: 50% Main crowdsale: early November      What is TechBench? TechBench is a social network for IT-professionals and programmers which will offer membership to specialists that can lead to an unlimited amount of opportunity to blend talents and ideas into meaningful projects. It combines the best of social media, crowd-based development, freelance employment and interactive crowdfunding. Users of the platform will be able to interact, exchange ideas, and work together to create technical foundations for startups.  TechBench brings together three user categories: investors, IT professionals and businesses. Because it's not merely a social network, but a crowdfunding and employment platform, TechBench provides an excellent opportunity for Ethereum-based investors to find high-quality projects and businesses to make contracts with IT professionals who come together to develop their own startups.  Social network TechBench is designed to become one of the main networks for IT specialists and programmers. Using the social profile, technology professionals will be able to show their qualifications, achievements, and areas of current interest. The social profile will offer wide opportunities for specialists to express themselves. Freelance participants will be able to join the platform to earn cash or value; they can also share ideas, join teams and collaborate on projects.  Investment portal TechBench allows everyone to safely fund start-ups with high growth potential. This approach maximizes opportunity for professionals, developer, and investors to gain access to substantial projects and early stage startups. With its base in smart contracts, it offers high levels of safety and investor comfort. The highest returns on investment often come from early stage investments. Investors that seek to maximize profits look to this stage as the best opportunity to get in on the ground floor of a successful startup.  Employment solution Employers seeking to fill gaps in their professional workforce can use TechBench to get vetted lists of qualified applicants. Professionals that create profiles gain exposure to employment and contract opportunities. The platform will give access for small and mediumsized (SMB) IT-business to the base of qualified IT specialists, formed using algorithms for screening and testing staff.  Platform intended to change current model of interaction in the freelance industry An innovative model will allow developers to be independent, work for themselves or find colleagues, search and create projects more efficiently. The opportunity to participate and invest in high-profit start-ups should become accessible to a wide audience. In addition, the platform will provide a system which gives access to the base of qualified IT specialists which is a recruiting solution for business clients.  TechBench is designed to completely change the way the freelance market works today. Instead of all of the users competing against one another for jobs, they will be able to come together to improve code and even develop their own new projects and ideas.  This new model is a ground breaking approach for promoting startups and creating early bird investment opportunities. Professionals that choose to share ideas create the possibility to grow through collaboration and not just through competition. It is precise and comprehensive solution to connecting investment and technical innovation, promoting ownership and long-term equity.  Collaboration rather than competition An innovative model will allow developers to be independent, work for themselves or find colleagues, search and create projects more efficiently. Collaboration is a distinctive feature of TechBench, and the ecosystem thrives on professional collaboration. Development sites allow people to share and combine code to produce great apps and programs. And crowdfunding sites are the basis for some of the most exciting and innovative products and startups in today's economy. TechBench brings all of these together under one roof - united with the power of Ethereum-based cryptocurrency.  Collaboration rather than competition is an ideal environment for developing projects. With a global talent pool, professionals can share ideas and promote technological innovation. Projects that take form can attract developers on the TechBench platform. Developers play the key role of fostering project development and connecting the project to potential funding sources.  More info TechBench isn't only a crypto-currency platform and a new style of freelance market; it's also a social network that allows IT specialists and early adopters of this advanced and exciting technology to come together and form social connections that enable innovation, project support and technical development.   TechBench hosts a professional social network that highlights work achievements and provides space to showcase projects. The framework for connections here is based on mutual professional interests, particularly in IT and related tech fields. Because TechBench is dedicated to creating a social network that truly meets the needs of tech specialists, developers and programmers, the capacities of each member's profile will be fully developed in order to allow each participant to fully show off their skills and shine, like an online portfolio, business card and presentation in one.   The TechBench social network will also include extensive communication capacities, including private messaging, voice calls and voice recordings and video chat, bringing in the most beloved features of everyday social networks to a professional space oriented to tech high achievers.   Some advantages of the TechBench social network will include:  Maximum Connectivity - TechBench allows you to search for and connect with fellow IT and computer professionals. Connect through mutual acquaintances and colleagues in a truly social network that allows you to connect with fellow specialists you already know and expand your sphere of knowledge by forging new connections.  Professional Portfolios - Combining the best features of sites like Behance and Dribbble but with a focus on IT professionals, TechBench allows you to show off your work, link to your projects and display your open-source code.   High-Quality Contacts - A profile on TechBench can help to define you as an IT professional. Like a LinkedIn page for the workplace in general, TechBench is an essential place for skilled technologists to come together and a mark of achievement and competence.  Communication Excellence - TechBench isn't only a place to show off your high number of connections, search for a job or connect to your co-workers. It's also a place where you can engage in private messaging, audio chat and even video chat. You won't need to head to Facebook or WhatsApp to connect with your friends and colleagues.  Job Searching Innovation - Because TechBench's social network is fully integrated with our freelance portal, you'll be seamlessly able to make new job connections and start contracts directly from our social network. Receive, negotiate and accept job offers from within your social network while expanding your employment opportunities.  Investment Potential - A site like TechBench, with full portfolio capacities to display not only past work but future projects, can also be a place to arrange investment and find partners for your next tech development project. Our network also includes skilled investors with a high level of IT knowledge. You can make the connections your startup needs on TechBench.  Collaborative Development - Just as the TechBench network is a great place for skilled technologists and investors to come together and communicate, it is highly developed for team and group communications. From multi-party video conference calls to running group chats for your project or business, you'll hardly need to connect on Slack when it's all in front of you at TechBench.  Designed for maximum business potential, professional networking and innovative tech projects, TechBench sets a new standard for any IT professional's online identity. With a TechBench profile, you'll be prepared to unlock the power of social networking for unprecedented innovation and development.  Platform aimed at different user categories  __ Investors  TechBench model offers opportunities for early investment and for investors to take a stake in the startup.  Investing with a long view is the best way to maximize profits, and the transparency features of the TechBench platform helps investors make funding decisions. __ IT specialists  IT professionals can work together and present their effort in a form that protects their intellectual property.  The developer has powerful incentives. They own a piece of the startup and they get paid when the project meets the milestones set by the development plan. __ Business (B2B)  B2B recruitment solution provides businesses pre-screened listing of qualified candidates that are ready to be hired.  TechBench eliminates the risk of inappropriate hires while reducing the time and effort needed to make a successful acquisition. __   CROWDSALE  1 TBCH = 0.001 ETH fixed price + Bonus part  Two-time emission is planned. Will be distributed in the following way:  Pre-ICO round: 5.100.000 TBCH tokens (10%). Soft cap: 500 ETH. Hard cap: 5 100 ETH.  ICO round: 51.000.000 TBCH tokens (75%), equals to 51 000 ETH.  Stage bonuses: Pre-ICO (presale) bonus to tokens is 50%. First 10 days: 20%. Second 10 days: 10%. The rest of the days - no bonus.  The TBCH token supply will be allocated as follows: 10% of TBCH tokens (5,100,000) will be distributed during the Pre-ICO (presale) 75% of TBCH tokens (51,000,000) will be distributed during the ICO (main crowdsale) 14% of TBCH tokens (8,400,000) will be distributed among founders 1% of TBCH tokens (600,000) will be used for bounty campaign  The source code for the ICO smart contract is publicly available for research in the Github repository at the following link: https://github.com/TechBenchMe/TGE  TOKEN  Holders of TBCH token will receive service platform commission, which is levied from investors when they finance development teams.  The ETH commission from each transaction on the service platform is quarterly transferred to a special smart contract that proportionally distributes the ETH between the holders of the token, in accordance with the number of tokens owned by each holder.
